<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1072] Nested embeddable with a relationship to an Entity with a generated id doesn&apos;t persist the relationship</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1072</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When working with embeddables I found that if I define a unidirectional @ManyToOne relationship from an embeddable to an Entity which has a generated id, the relationship in the join table doesn&apos;t get persisted. I&apos;ll attach a zip with my code, but I&apos;ll also try to describe the scenario here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Entities: &lt;br/&gt;
Seller - Has an auto generated ID and a name&lt;br/&gt;
Book - Has an id(isbn) and an ElementCollection of Listings&lt;br/&gt;
Listing - An embeddable that has a ManyToOne relationship to Seller, a price and comments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The scenario is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Create all the sellers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Create a book.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add a listing to each book. Each listing takes a Seller Entity and a price.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When I commit the book, the seller_id column in my Listing join table is always zero.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</description>
